128
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,670
Hypothermia and pregnancy.

129
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:54,230
This is important because hypothermia puts
your baby at risk for neural tube defects.

130
00:07:54,230 --> 00:07:57,920
What happens is within the six, first six
weeks of pregnancy,

131
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:02,960
a neural tube birth defect is an opening
in the spinal cord or brain of a baby.

132
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:06,670
The early spinal cord of the embryo begins
as a flat layer of cells,

133
00:08:06,670 --> 00:08:11,530
which rolls into a tube 28 days after the
baby is conceived.

134
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:14,910
This process can be impacted by high body
temperature and

135
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:17,930
many women don't even know that they're
pregnant that early.

136
00:08:17,930 --> 00:08:19,650
This is especially problematic for

137
00:08:19,650 --> 00:08:23,600
female endurance athletes like marathon
runners, who frequently get their core

138
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:28,460
